<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="432" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d432">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 811.304M28/63.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-02">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">March</hi> 2, 1912</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The Navy Department highly appreciates the honor contained in article
                            four of the President’s decree, relating to delivery by the Cuban Navy
                            on board an American war vessel of the remains taken from the <hi rend="italic">Maine</hi>. It would, however, be practically more
                            expedient for the American Navy to receive the caskets at Caballería
                            wharf and convey them to the <hi rend="italic">North Carolina</hi>. You
                            will urge upon the Cuban Government a modification of the arrangements
                            to this effect.</p>
                        <p>The wreck of the <hi rend="italic">Maine</hi> will probably not be
                            removed before March 14.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>